Bevy Version: 0.14 (upcoming / release candidate) 当前双语版本对应的是: 3d540e7, 日期: 2024/06/13, 等双语版本整个翻译完之后,再处理原始仓库的更新 This page is an overview, to give you an idea of the big picture of how Bevy works. Click on the various links to be taken to dedicated pages where you can learn more about each concept. 这里只是概述,细节需要点击链接进一步查看. As mentioned in the ECS Intro , Bevy manages all of your functionality/behaviors for you, running them when appropriate and giving them access to whatever parts of your data they need. Individual pieces of functionality are called systems . Each system is a Rust function (fn) you write, which accepts special parameter types to indicate what data it needs to access. Think of the function signature as a "specification" for what to fetch from the ECS World . Here is what a system might look like. Note how, just by looking at the function parameters, we know exactly what data can be accessed. fn enemy_detect_player( // access data from resources mut ai_settings: ResMut<EnemyAiSettings>, gamemode: Res<GameModeData>, // access data from entities/components query_player: Query<&Transform, With<Player>>, query_enemies: Query<&mut Transform, (With<Enemy>, Without<Player>)>, // in case we want to spawn/despawn entities, etc. mut commands: Commands,
) { // ... implement your behavior here ...
