This is the more formal and powerful way to use system sets. You can create a Rust type (struct or enum) to serve as a label/identifier, so you can refer to the set from different places. For a single set, create an empty struct. If you need to create multiple related sets, create an enum. Every variant of the enum is a separate system set. You need to derive SystemSet + an assortment of required standard Rust traits: #[derive(SystemSet, Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
