Queries support parallel iteration to let you process many entities across multiple CPU threads. fn my_particle_physics( mut q_particles: Query<(&mut Transform, &MyParticleState), With<MyParticle>>,
) { q_particles.par_iter_mut().for_each(|(mut transform, my_state)| { my_state.move_particle(&mut transform); });
} One limitation of parallel iteration is that safe Rust does not allow you to share &mut access across CPU threads. Therefore, it is not possible to mutate any data outside of the current entity's own components . If you need to mutate shared data, you could use something like Mutex , but beware of the added overhead. It could easily drown out any benefits you get from parallel iteration.

