As of Bevy 0.12, a workaround is needed for building with MSVC. If you use the MSVC toolchain, the blake3 dependency assumes you are building on Windows and tries to run some EXEs during its build process, which do not exist in the Linux cross-compilation environment. The solution is to tell it to not do that and use pure Rust code instead. Set an environment variable when building: export CARGO_FEATURE_PURE=1
cargo build --target=x86_64-pc-windows-msvc --release Or add blake3 to your Cargo.toml if you want to persist the configuration: [dependencies]
blake3 = { version = "1.5", features = [ "pure" ] }

